-- Rexam to Get Up to 350 Million Pounds From Unit Sale, Times Says
-- B y   K a t i e   L i n s e l l
-- 2012-02-19T10:51:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-19/rexam-to-get-up-to-350-million-pounds-from-unit-sale-times-says.html
Rexam Plc (REX) , a maker of drinks cans
and packaging materials, is likely to announce the sale of its
plastics division this week, the Sunday Times reported, citing
analysts.  Rexam may get as much as 350 million pounds ($554 million)
from the sale, according to research by Bank of America Merrill
Lynch, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katie Linsell in London at 
